@startuml
title UML State Chart Diagram - Ott Based System Mini Reel

[*] --> CreateAccount

state CreateAccount <<choice>>
CreateAccount : [User already has an account?]
CreateAccount --> NoAccount : [No]
CreateAccount --> AlreadyLoggedIn : [Yes, but not watching a video]

state NoAccount
NoAccount : do / prompt user to create an account
NoAccount --> CreateSuccess : [Account created successfully]
NoAccount --> CreateFailure : [Failed to create account]

state AlreadyLoggedIn
AlreadyLoggedIn : do / check if the user is watching a video
AlreadyLoggedIn --> WatchingVideo : [Yes, user is already watching a video]
AlreadyLoggedIn --> NotWatchingVideo : [No, user is not watching a video]

state WatchingVideo
WatchingVideo : do / allow user to watch the video
WatchingVideo : [User wants to save the video in their likes list?]
WatchingVideo --> SaveLike : [Yes]
WatchingVideo --> ContinueWatching : [No]

state SaveLike
SaveLike : do / add the video to the user's likes list
SaveLike --> Success : [Saved successfully]
SaveLike --> Failure : [Failed to save the video]

state ContinueWatching
ContinueWatching : do / continue watching the video
ContinueWatching : [User wants to leave the discussion option?]
ContinueWatching --> Discussion : [Yes]
ContinueWatching --> NotDiscussion : [No]

state Discussion
Discussion : do / enter the discussion option
Discussion : [User wants to exit the discussion option?]
Discussion --> ExitDiscussion : [Yes]
Discussion --> ContinueDiscussion : [No]

state ExitDiscussion
ExitDiscussion : do / exit the discussion option and return to watching the video
ExitDiscussion --> WatchingVideo

state NotDiscussion
NotDiscussion : do / continue watching the video without entering the discussion option
NotDiscussion --> WatchingVideo

state LikesList
LikesList : entry / entered the app
LikesList : do / display saved videos in the user's likes list
LikesList : exit / viewed saved videos

@enduml
